WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.450 --> 00:00:05.140
Twenty years before the main story of Game
of Thrones, there was a great tournament held

00:00:05.140 --> 00:00:10.410
at the castle of Harrenhal . This was like,
the biggest high school house party in Westeros

00:00:10.410 --> 00:00:15.900
– everyone was there, drinking, feasting,
hanging out, hooking up, trading secrets,

00:00:15.900 --> 00:00:20.550
raising drama – and all these years later,
people are still talking about what happened

00:00:20.550 --> 00:00:25.310
those nights – who got the most drunk, who
hooked up with who, who was plotting to overthrow

00:00:25.310 --> 00:00:29.990
the government – that sorta stuff . We don’t
know the details of much that happened, cause

00:00:29.990 --> 00:00:32.759
we only learn of the tourney through memory
and rumour.

00:00:32.759 --> 00:00:38.620
But we do hear one mysterious story – about
the Knight of the Laughing Tree.

00:00:38.620 --> 00:00:42.329
In Book 3, Meera Reed tells Bran Stark the
story.

00:00:42.329 --> 00:00:47.989
It begins in the Neck, a swampy region north
of the riverlands . The story follows a crannogman

00:00:47.989 --> 00:00:52.390
– a young man from the Neck, and though
Meera never says his name, it’s implied

00:00:52.390 --> 00:00:57.300
that the lad is a young Howland Reed – the
father of Meera and Jojen.

00:00:57.300 --> 00:01:01.860
From his home in the Neck, Howland travelled
south to the Isle of Faces, an island in the

00:01:01.860 --> 00:01:07.639
riverlands sacred to the old gods and inhabited
by a mysterious people called the green men

00:01:07.639 --> 00:01:12.759
. Howland stayed there through winter, and
when he left, he came to castle of Harrenhal,

00:01:12.759 --> 00:01:15.119
where the tournament was beginning.

00:01:15.119 --> 00:01:18.789
Meera lists some of the people who were there
– and again she doesn’t say their names,

00:01:18.789 --> 00:01:21.679
but we can figure them out by their titles
and heraldry.

00:01:21.679 --> 00:01:27.119
There’s “The king”, Aerys Targaryen,
“with his son the dragon prince” Rhaegar

00:01:27.119 --> 00:01:32.200
– cause this all takes place before Robert’s
Rebellion when the Targaryens still ruled

00:01:32.200 --> 00:01:33.200
Westeros.

00:01:33.200 --> 00:01:36.939
There are “The White Swords” – the Kingsguard
– who’d come “to welcome a new brother

00:01:36.939 --> 00:01:40.969
to their ranks” – a young Jaime Lannister
was about to join the Kingsguard.

00:01:40.969 --> 00:01:45.529
“The storm lord”, Robert Baratheon was
there, “and the rose lord”, Mace Tyrell.

00:01:45.529 --> 00:01:50.240
But “The great lion of the rock”, Tywin
Lannister, didn’t come – he was angry

00:01:50.240 --> 00:01:56.189
with Aerys for taking Jaime into the Kingsguard,
and for refusing to marry Rhaegar to Cersei

00:01:56.189 --> 00:02:00.939
– Rhaegar instead married Elia Martell,
she’s here as well.

00:02:00.939 --> 00:02:06.029
So the young Howland from the Neck saw all
these important people at this great castle,

00:02:06.029 --> 00:02:10.891
the knights and banners, the food and laughter
, and he was excited to be a part of it . But

00:02:10.891 --> 00:02:15.069
as he was “walking across [a] field”,
“enjoying the … day and harming none”,

00:02:15.069 --> 00:02:20.310
he was attacked by three young squires . There’s
a lot of racism against the crannogmen of

00:02:20.310 --> 00:02:24.909
the Neck – people call them “mud-men”
and “frog-eaters” . The squires believed

00:02:24.909 --> 00:02:29.290
this was their world, and the crannogman Howland
“had no right to be there”.

00:02:29.290 --> 00:02:34.189
So they hit him and kicked him and cursed
him until he was saved by a “she-wolf”

00:02:34.189 --> 00:02:35.819
– Lyanna Stark.

00:02:35.819 --> 00:02:40.849
Lyanna drove off the squires with a blunted
sword and took Howland back her tent to treat

00:02:40.849 --> 00:02:41.849
his injuries.

00:02:41.849 --> 00:02:47.340
There, Howland met Lyanna’s brothers – “the
wild wolf” Brandon Stark – who dies before

00:02:47.340 --> 00:02:52.170
Robert’s Rebellion so he isn’t in the
show – “the quiet wolf” Eddard Stark,

00:02:52.170 --> 00:02:56.920
and “the pup” Benjen Stark . They’re
all teenagers back then – Brandon’s about

00:02:56.920 --> 00:03:01.659
nineteen, Ned was eighteen, Lyanna bout fifteen
and Benjen about fourteen.

00:03:01.659 --> 00:03:03.549
Howland was sixteen or so.

00:03:03.549 --> 00:03:07.920
Lyanna insisted that Howland come sit with
the Starks at the feast, so that night “he

00:03:07.920 --> 00:03:11.950
ate and drank with the” northmen, and took
in the sights of the feast.

00:03:11.950 --> 00:03:17.560
He saw Prince Rhaegar sing “a song so sad
it made” Lyanna cry – this is the first

00:03:17.560 --> 00:03:20.180
mention of a connection between these two.

00:03:20.180 --> 00:03:25.459
And he saw “a maid with laughing purple
eyes”, Ashara Dayne, dance with a Kingsguard,

00:03:25.459 --> 00:03:31.280
and with Oberyn Martell, and Jon Connington,
and with Ned Stark – after Ned got Brandon

00:03:31.280 --> 00:03:37.010
to ask Ashara for the dance, cause Ned was
too shy . There are rumours of a relationship

00:03:37.010 --> 00:03:41.459
between Ned and Ashara – some say that Ned
got Ashara pregnant, others think it might

00:03:41.459 --> 00:03:46.920
have been Brandon – whoever it was, a year
later, Ashara had a stillborn child, and her

00:03:46.920 --> 00:03:52.980
brother Arthur was killed – by Ned and Howland
– and Ashara committed suicide – so we

00:03:52.980 --> 00:03:55.329
might never know the truth.

00:03:55.329 --> 00:03:59.219
Later at the feast, Howland spotted the squires
who attacked him, and saw they each served

00:03:59.219 --> 00:04:04.249
a knight – one of House Haigh, one of House
Blount, and one of House Frey . The Starks

00:04:04.249 --> 00:04:08.660
suggested that Howland should win back his
honour by beating the knights in the tournament

00:04:08.660 --> 00:04:12.670
– but Howland wasn’t much good at riding
and jousting and thought he’d just make

00:04:12.670 --> 00:04:14.299
a fool of himself.

00:04:14.299 --> 00:04:18.950
That night he went out by the lake and looked
to the Isle of Faces and prayed to the old

00:04:18.950 --> 00:04:20.810
gods of the north.

00:04:20.810 --> 00:04:25.581
Later at the tournament, the knights of Haigh,
Blount and Frey did well in the jousting,

00:04:25.581 --> 00:04:30.300
but late one afternoon, a new challenger appeared
– a mystery knight, with his name and face

00:04:30.300 --> 00:04:36.580
hidden, identified only by weirwood tree with
a laughing face painted on his shield.

00:04:36.580 --> 00:04:41.560
This Knight of the Laughing Tree challenged
the Haigh, Blount and Frey knights, and defeated

00:04:41.560 --> 00:04:43.420
each of them at jousting.

00:04:43.420 --> 00:04:47.470
He gave them back their horses and armour
only after the knights punished their squires

00:04:47.470 --> 00:04:52.130
for having attacked Howland – and so the
crannogman’s honour was restored, and all

00:04:52.130 --> 00:04:54.920
the crowd cheered for the mystery knight.

00:04:54.920 --> 00:04:57.320
King Aerys, though, was not a fan.

00:04:57.320 --> 00:05:02.950
Aerys was mad, and paranoid, and he saw the
Tree Knight as his enemy – so he sent his

00:05:02.950 --> 00:05:08.070
son Rhaegar to find out who the Tree Knight
was, but apparently “all they ever found

00:05:08.070 --> 00:05:11.720
was [the Knight’s] painted shield, hanging
… in a tree”.

00:05:11.720 --> 00:05:18.200
And so the story of the Knight of the Laughing
Tree ends with a mystery – who was the knight?

00:05:18.200 --> 00:05:22.640
The story leads us to believe that the Knight
was Howland Reed – and Howland would fit

00:05:22.640 --> 00:05:25.380
some of the details we’re given about the
Knight.

00:05:25.380 --> 00:05:29.591
The Knight’s said to be “short of stature”
and Howland was “small” , and the Knight

00:05:29.591 --> 00:05:34.440
is “clad in ill-fitting armor made up of
bits and pieces” , as Howland would’ve

00:05:34.440 --> 00:05:37.030
been if had to scrounge armour together to
compete.

00:05:37.030 --> 00:05:42.380
But we’re also told pretty clearly that
Howland isn’t good at riding and jousting

00:05:42.380 --> 00:05:47.160
– he feared he’d make a fool of himself
if he entered the tourney . In the story Meera

00:05:47.160 --> 00:05:51.750
suggests that the old gods or the green men
of the Isle heard Howland’s prayers by the

00:05:51.750 --> 00:05:56.240
lake , and “gave strength to his arm”
so he could win back his honour.

00:05:56.240 --> 00:05:58.620
Which is nice enough for a fairytale.

00:05:58.620 --> 00:06:03.211
But Game of Thrones isn’t the sort of world
where the weak can beat the strong by just

00:06:03.211 --> 00:06:06.530
being righteous and brave and believing in
themselves.

00:06:06.530 --> 00:06:11.320
Littlefinger learned that in his duel with
Brandon Stark . As for the old gods, they

00:06:11.320 --> 00:06:16.270
really don’t seem to be the benevolent divine
intervention sorta type – they’re more

00:06:16.270 --> 00:06:22.000
into blood sacrifice, all that heavy Old Testament
shit . Would they really bother answering

00:06:22.000 --> 00:06:24.940
the prayers of a teenager who wants to win
a joust?

00:06:24.940 --> 00:06:30.220
That’s just isn’t consistent with what
we’ve seen of gods and magic in this series.

00:06:30.220 --> 00:06:34.410
The other important reason why the Knight
probably isn’t Howland is because Bran tells

00:06:34.410 --> 00:06:37.150
us that he thinks the Knight is Howland.

00:06:37.150 --> 00:06:41.380
What sort of mystery is that, if we’re immediately
given the right answer?

00:06:41.380 --> 00:06:45.260
Usually the way mysteries work in this series
is that we’re given an obvious answer at

00:06:45.260 --> 00:06:51.060
first – like, that Jon Snow is the bastard
son of Ned Stark, or that Jon Arryn was poisoned

00:06:51.060 --> 00:06:55.870
by the Lannisters – but we later find out
that the truth is something more complex – that

00:06:55.870 --> 00:07:01.370
Jon Snow is actually Lyanna Stark’s son,
and that Jon Arryn was actually poisoned by

00:07:01.370 --> 00:07:03.130
Lysa, for Littlefinger.

00:07:03.130 --> 00:07:07.750
So what’s the deeper, more complex truth
to the mystery of the Knight of the Laughing

00:07:07.750 --> 00:07:09.210
Tree?

00:07:09.210 --> 00:07:14.160
When Meera tells this story, Jojen seems really
surprised that Bran hasn’t already heard

00:07:14.160 --> 00:07:20.170
the tale from his father Ned . This may suggest
that Ned, or someone close to him was the

00:07:20.170 --> 00:07:21.570
mystery knight.

00:07:21.570 --> 00:07:23.140
Maybe it was one of the Stark boys.

00:07:23.140 --> 00:07:27.950
Benjen, Ned and Brandon each would’ve made
a better knight than Howland Reed.

00:07:27.950 --> 00:07:32.860
The Starks were trained to ride and fight,
so they wouldn’t have needed divine intervention

00:07:32.860 --> 00:07:35.250
to plausibly win a few jousts.

00:07:35.250 --> 00:07:39.570
Brandon, especially, was said to be good at
riding and fighting, and he was described

00:07:39.570 --> 00:07:44.830
as hot-blooded, and rash – a “gallant
fool” . So standing up for Howland by riding

00:07:44.830 --> 00:07:48.990
in the tourney fits pretty well with what
we know of his personality.

00:07:48.990 --> 00:07:53.620
There are problems with Brandon, though, cause
Brandon was “tall” , so even at the age

00:07:53.620 --> 00:07:57.510
of nineteen, he might not have fit the mystery
knight’s short stature.

00:07:57.510 --> 00:08:02.090
Also, it doesn’t make much sense for Brandon
to enter the tourney as a mystery knight,

00:08:02.090 --> 00:08:07.750
cause he later rides in the tourney as himself
– why would he choose to ride in disguise

00:08:07.750 --> 00:08:09.750
in the first place?

00:08:09.750 --> 00:08:11.700
Another possibility is Ned.

00:08:11.700 --> 00:08:16.440
He was younger and shorter than Brandon , so
he might fit the Knight’s small stature.

00:08:16.440 --> 00:08:21.080
And Ned riding for Howland in the tourney
might help explain how Howland became such

00:08:21.080 --> 00:08:26.670
a loyal friend to Ned . However, even as a
young man Ned’s described as “solemn”

00:08:26.670 --> 00:08:30.960
and “somber” . He’s responsible and
reserved, with “a certain distaste for the

00:08:30.960 --> 00:08:35.860
… pageantry of tourneys” . Joining in
a joust as a mystery knight, with a shield

00:08:35.860 --> 00:08:39.380
of a “laughing” tree is not exactly Ned’s
style.

00:08:39.380 --> 00:08:41.860
He’s not so showy and theatrical.

00:08:41.860 --> 00:08:46.750
So Ned’s not a great fit for the Knight
of the Laughing Tree either.

00:08:46.750 --> 00:08:48.050
Maybe it was Benjen.

00:08:48.050 --> 00:08:52.570
Benjen was fourteen or younger then, so he’d
fit the Knight’s short stature.

00:08:52.570 --> 00:08:57.190
And Benjen was the one to offer Howland armour
and horse to ride in the tourney , so he was

00:08:57.190 --> 00:08:59.950
enthusiastic about someone competing.

00:08:59.950 --> 00:09:05.250
But on the other hand, at fourteen years of
age, Ben was very young and there’s no suggestion

00:09:05.250 --> 00:09:10.250
in the text that he was particularly good
at riding or fighting or jousting so he doesn’t

00:09:10.250 --> 00:09:13.070
seem a very likely Knight either.

00:09:13.070 --> 00:09:18.570
All three Stark boys could maybe be the Tree
Knight, but none are very convincing.

00:09:18.570 --> 00:09:22.440
A more likely answer to this mystery is Lyanna
Stark.

00:09:22.440 --> 00:09:27.410
As a teenage girl, Lyanna could fit the Knight’s
short stature, and “ill-fitting armor”.

00:09:27.410 --> 00:09:31.970
And she certainly has motivation to help Howland
– she was the one to come defend him in

00:09:31.970 --> 00:09:33.350
the first place.

00:09:33.350 --> 00:09:37.790
Competing in the tourney also fits well with
her personality – she’s described as “wild”,

00:09:37.790 --> 00:09:42.090
“willful”, and “boyish” , she’s
said to be like Arya – and fighting to help

00:09:42.090 --> 00:09:45.690
out a friend is exactly the sort of thing
Arya would do.

00:09:45.690 --> 00:09:49.920
Lyanna being the Knight also adds a cool twist
in having the Knight who everyone assumed

00:09:49.920 --> 00:09:52.380
to be a man turn out to be a girl.

00:09:52.380 --> 00:09:56.130
At one point in the story Meera describes
the Knight’s voice “booming” through

00:09:56.130 --> 00:10:01.490
his helm – maybe the echoeyness of the Knight’s
helmet helped disguise Lyanna’s voice.

00:10:01.490 --> 00:10:05.900
Of course, it is questionable whether a fifteen
year old girl would be strong enough to use

00:10:05.900 --> 00:10:11.300
a lance in a joust , but in Winds, there’s
another fifteen-year-old girl, Elia Sand,

00:10:11.300 --> 00:10:17.110
who jousts so much they call her Lady Lance
– a perfect precedent for Lyanna to joust

00:10:17.110 --> 00:10:18.110
also.

00:10:18.110 --> 00:10:22.590
Further, we’re told a bunch of times that
Lyanna was a very good horse rider – Roose

00:10:22.590 --> 00:10:28.070
Bolton says that Lyanna “was half a horse”,
and he also says in the same paragraph that

00:10:28.070 --> 00:10:34.200
“A great jouster must be a great horseman”
. Jaime Lannister agrees, thinking that jousting

00:10:34.200 --> 00:10:39.920
is three-quarters horsemanship . The text
directly links the idea of riding being important

00:10:39.920 --> 00:10:45.670
for jousting to the fact that Lyanna was great
at riding – a pretty strong hint that Lyanna

00:10:45.670 --> 00:10:47.890
could have done well in a tourney.

00:10:47.890 --> 00:10:52.120
So Lyanna fits the Knight of the Laughing
Tree quite well – but the most convincing

00:10:52.120 --> 00:10:56.670
reasons for why Lyanna was probably the mystery
knight relate to how this would fit with the

00:10:56.670 --> 00:10:57.990
broader story.

00:10:57.990 --> 00:11:03.460
It’s very very interesting that we’re
specifically told that King Aerys sent his

00:11:03.460 --> 00:11:07.890
son Rhaegar to find and unmask the Knight
of the Laughing Tree.

00:11:07.890 --> 00:11:12.880
Because later in this same tournament, Prince
Rhaegar publicly crowns Lyanna as his Queen

00:11:12.880 --> 00:11:18.070
of Love and Beauty, and later, he runs away
with Lyanna, leading to Robert’s Rebellion

00:11:18.070 --> 00:11:22.700
, the deaths of Rhaegar and Lyanna, and the
birth of Jon Snow.

00:11:22.700 --> 00:11:28.320
Maybe the fateful relationship between Lyanna
and Rhaegar all began when Rhaegar was sent

00:11:28.320 --> 00:11:30.460
to find the Knight of the Laughing Tree.

00:11:30.460 --> 00:11:35.420
We’re told that no one found the Knight,
but what if Rhaegar did and chose to keep

00:11:35.420 --> 00:11:37.029
Lyanna’s secret?

00:11:37.029 --> 00:11:40.470
Maybe he was impressed by her boldness in
riding in the tourney.

00:11:40.470 --> 00:11:44.320
We already know Lyanna wept at the beauty
of Rhaegar’s harp earlier.

00:11:44.320 --> 00:11:45.320
Maybe they hit it off.

00:11:45.320 --> 00:11:49.529
They say there’s nothing “like a tourney
to make the blood run hot” – so “maybe

00:11:49.529 --> 00:11:55.160
some words were whispered in a tent of a night”,
“Words or kisses, maybe more” maybe this

00:11:55.160 --> 00:12:00.030
is how Lyanna and Rhaegar, ice and fire, first
fell in love.

00:12:00.030 --> 00:12:04.160
It’s also very interesting that the place
where all this happens, and the place where

00:12:04.160 --> 00:12:10.000
Rhaegar later quote-unquote abducts Lyanna
is so close to the Isle of Faces.

00:12:10.000 --> 00:12:14.190
There are theories that Rhaegar and Lyanna
secretly got married on the Isle of Faces,

00:12:14.190 --> 00:12:18.980
with the weirwoods all round – so that psychic
Bran can later have a vision of the wedding

00:12:18.980 --> 00:12:22.860
and R+L=J can finally be revealed.

00:12:22.860 --> 00:12:28.130
This all very speculative, but it fits so
well with what we know, and paints a beautiful

00:12:28.130 --> 00:12:33.611
picture of a tragic love story between Lyanna
Stark and Rhaegar Targaryen, a story that

00:12:33.611 --> 00:12:38.830
all begins with the Knight of the Laughing
Tree.

00:12:38.830 --> 00:12:43.120
So given how well this all fits, and given
the hints of Lyanna’s riding ability and

00:12:43.120 --> 00:12:47.180
personality, it seems pretty likely that Lyanna
is our mystery knight.

00:12:47.180 --> 00:12:51.610
But we’ll also have a quick look at a crazier
theory.

00:12:51.610 --> 00:12:56.680
As we saw in Season 6, Bran Stark’s greensight
tree-magic psychic powers can lead to some

00:12:56.680 --> 00:13:01.540
pretty wacky timey-wimey shenanigans, like
when he broke the mind of Hodor by reaching

00:13:01.540 --> 00:13:06.670
through his past self to make the Hodor of
the present “hold the door”.

00:13:06.670 --> 00:13:10.040
Some fans believe that something similar could
have happened with the Knight of the Laughing

00:13:10.040 --> 00:13:15.839
Tree – that when Howland prayed to the old
gods, Bran answers his prayers from the future

00:13:15.839 --> 00:13:21.670
by warging into past-Howland, taking the identity
of the mystery knight – with a weirwood

00:13:21.670 --> 00:13:27.250
on his shield – and using some manner of
old gods magic to win the jousts and restore

00:13:27.250 --> 00:13:29.130
Howland’s honour.

00:13:29.130 --> 00:13:33.850
This fits some of the talk of magic mentioned
in Meera’s story , and it also gives Bran

00:13:33.850 --> 00:13:39.680
the chance to be something he’s always dreamed
of being – a knight . After Meera tells

00:13:39.680 --> 00:13:43.780
the story of the Tree Knight, Bran thinks
that he’d love to be a knight for a day.

00:13:43.780 --> 00:13:46.770
“A day would be enough”, he thinks.

00:13:46.770 --> 00:13:52.000
Maybe with the magic of the old gods he got
that one day at the tourney of Harrenhal.

00:13:52.000 --> 00:13:57.430
So yeah the magic time-travel theories are
kinda ridiculous, but it has happened before,

00:13:57.430 --> 00:14:01.190
and these ideas can have some nice thematic
resonance.

00:14:01.190 --> 00:14:04.040
But it was probably Lyanna.

00:14:04.040 --> 00:14:07.990
We’ll talk more about Lyanna and Rhaegar
before Season 7 arrives, but you might like

00:14:07.990 --> 00:14:12.670
to go back and watch the Season 6 Episode
10 video – Rhaegar and Lyanna and Jon are

00:14:12.670 --> 00:14:15.120
explained about 14 minutes in.

00:14:15.120 --> 00:14:16.839
Thanks for watching this video.

00:14:16.839 --> 00:14:21.120
As ever, these theories and ideas mostly come
from the Game of Thrones fan community – go

00:14:21.120 --> 00:14:24.330
check out westeros.org and the subreddits.

00:14:24.330 --> 00:14:28.570
Thanks to the translators for translating
captions, thanks to The Mico for use of his

00:14:28.570 --> 00:14:33.640
art, and thanks to the Patrons who make Alt
Shift X possible, including Paige Marchus-Stewart,

00:14:33.640 --> 00:14:38.840
Natalie Woo, Jason Gray Jr, Walt Mayfield,
and History of Westeros – a podcast you

00:14:38.840 --> 00:14:41.279
should all check out, link below.

00:14:41.279 --> 00:14:41.699
Cheers!

